<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dickinson</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-02-28"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 28, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>Inclosed herewith, I transmit you a copy of a dispatch<note n="*" xml:id="d374fn1">For inclosure see dispatch No. 1530 from Mr. Adams,
                                vol. I, p. 151.</note> recently received from Charles Francis Adams,
                            esq., in reference to the misunderstanding of the British government
                            with that of Nicaragua.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">A. B. Dickinson</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>